{"id":"aura-plugins-t8za","title":"S4-B1-MINOR: test_worker_phases_is_p9_only asserts inclusion only, not exclusion","description":"In test_context_injection.py::TestGetRoleContextWorker::test_worker_phases_is_p9_only (line 473), the test name claims 'is_p9_only' but the assertion only checks 'PhaseId.P9_SLICE in ctx.phases'. This would pass even if WORKER had multiple phases in its context.

From PHASE_SPECS, WORKER is only in P9_SLICE.owner_roles, so the production behavior is correct. However, the test does not enforce the 'only' part of its name: it should additionally assert that ctx.phases == frozenset({PhaseId.P9_SLICE}) or assert len(ctx.phases) == 1.

Remediation: Change the assertion to assert ctx.phases == frozenset({PhaseId.P9_SLICE}) to match the test's declared intent. This is a naming/assertion consistency issue.","status":"open","priority":2,"issue_type":"task","owner":"dayvidpham@gmail.com","created_at":"2026-02-23T04:28:54Z","created_by":"David Huu Pham","updated_at":"2026-02-23T04:28:54Z"}

{"id":"aura-plugins-f4n2","title":"S2-B1-MINOR: Diff presence test relies on wrapper header string, not actual diff content","description":"In test_gen_schema.py::TestDiffOutput::test_diff_shown_when_file_exists_and_changed (line 112), the assertion checks for '---' OR '+++' OR 'diff' in the captured stdout. The production code (gen_schema.py line 1740) prints a header 'f"\n--- Unified diff for {output} ---"' which contains '---' regardless of the actual diff content. While the production code only prints this header when diff_lines is non-empty (line 1739), the test assertion would trivially pass by matching the header string even if the body difflib.unified_diff output was absent.

Similarly, test_diff_output_is_unified_format accepts 'No changes' as valid, which means a test run where content is already identical would not catch a missing diff.

Remediation: The test should assert that at least one line starts with '+' or '-' (excluding the '---'/'+++' file headers), confirming that real changed lines are present in the diff body. This makes the test verify the substance of the diff, not just the header.","status":"open","priority":2,"issue_type":"task","owner":"dayvidpham@gmail.com","created_at":"2026-02-23T04:27:36Z","created_by":"David Huu Pham","updated_at":"2026-02-23T04:27:36Z"}

